They opened this location not far from where I live a while back, but I never had the time nor the desire to go. I finally went yesterday before work. Parking will generally be a problem in this busy location, although you can find a metered spot here & there. The atmosphere is very nice & the menu's a bit pricey: I had a nice-sized burger called the CEO & a red velvet shake for $16.81. The shake was very good, but you forget about everything else once you taste the burger. It's really good. I'm giving this place four stars just on the taste alone. It's got a unique taste to it, a bit sour. It's very juicy & greasy, and I loved it. If you don't like such food, it looks like they have other items that may be more suitable for you. This burger, however, is comparable to Shake Shack, which is a bold statement for me since I worship that place. My order came out fairly quickly, and I have no complaints.
